<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/414a</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-09T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            9, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>348. Please cable us text of ruble note which British are issuing at
                                Archangel, and keep us advised of method they are adopting to
                                introduce such notes into circulation, and to secure their
                                acceptance as circulating medium and their success in so doing.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>